Variables
*********
Variables are like containers. You can place data into variables and refer to the data in it by the name of the variable.

Strings
*******
Javascript strings store a series of characters. A string can be any text inside single quotes or double quotes.

Functions (arguments, return)
*****************************
Functions are set of instructions. The sequence of statements inside the function is  function body. Functions can be called to invoke their action. Optionally values can be passed to a function. These values are called arguments. Optionally they can return a value.


if statements
*************
if statements are used to check a condition. If the condition evaluates to true, then the given block of code for the condition is executed.

Boolean values (true, false)
****************************
Javascript Booleans represent one of two values - true or false.
